    {
      "title": "Teval Graveyard Value",
      "format": "commander",
      "goal": "This deck aims to use self-mill and land recursion through its commander, [[Teval, the Balanced Scale]] to build a powerful value engine that ramps lands, reanimates creatures, and compounds graveyard-based synergies.\n\nEarly game is spent ramping with synergistic ramp spells such as [[Skull Prophet]] and [[Harrow]], ramping quickly into Teval. Once Teval is out, begin building the engine through leave-the-graveyard effects such as [[Teval's Judgment]] and [[Kheru Goldkeeper]], or establish more self-mill and leave-graveyard-enabling effects such as [[Ripples of Undeath]], [[Colossal Grave-Reaver]] and [[Overlord of the Balemurk]].\n\nZombie tokens can optionally be used for sac fodder for enabling more powerful effects such as [[Victimize]] or other effects requiring a creature sacrifice, or become mana dorks through cards like [[Insidious Roots]].\n\nSimple highly-synergistic clusters of cards such as [[Life from the Loam]] and cycling lands ([[Lonely Sandbar]] , [[Tranquil Thicket]] , and [[Barren Moor]]) provide cheap access to efficient draw engines.\n\nWin through going wide with zombies, tall with a big Teval or heavy beaters like [[Archon of Cruelty]], or through infinite combos such as [[Kheru Goldkeeper]] and [[Tortured Existence]] for infinite zombies through Teval, or through infinite recursion effects like [[Gravecrawler]], [[Warren Soultrader]], and [[Cauldron of Essence]] to whittle all opponents down at once.\n\nWhile the deck has a number of play patterns with various win conditions, it values interactive games where it can apply pressure to opponents through disruption and counterspell effects over outright winning through uninteractive solitaire.",
      "commander": [
        {
          "name": "Teval, the Balanced Scale",
          "quantity": 1
        }
